      • processTemplate

        public CycObject processTemplate(DenotationalTerm querySpec,
                                 ElMt focalMt,
                                 Fort focalPredicateCollection,
                                 com.cyc.query.parameters.InferenceParameters overridingQueryProperties,
                                 Map<CycObject,Object> substitutions,
                                 int ipcQueueIdentifier,
                                 List<CycSymbol> ipcQueueElementSpecification,
                                 CycList<Object> toeProcessingOverrides)
                          throws CycConnectionException,
                                 CycApiException
        This function takes a query specification and iteratively uses the bindings from the query to make assertions. These assertions come from instances of #$TOEAssertSpecification associated with query spec via the predicate #$queryAssociatedTOEAssertSpecification in any microtheory.

        All parameters except querySpec and ipcQueueIdentifier have defaults for null.

        Parameters:
        querySpec - the query specification to process, an instance of #$CycLQuerySpecification. These can be created via getNewQueueId().
        focalMt - all assertions for predicates contained within focalPredicateCollection will be retrieved from this mt. Defaults to #$InferencePSC.
        focalPredicateCollection - the Collection of predicates for which to apply the focalMt. Must be #$Predicate or a spec thereof. Defaults to #$Predicate.
        overridingQueryProperties - a PLIST of overriding properties for the query. Defaults to no overridden properties.
        substitutions - an ALIST of (old . new) pairs to deal with indexicals. Defaults to no substitutions.
        ipcQueueIdentifier - an integer identifier used to specify which ipc-queue to setf results onto
        ipcQueueElementSpecification - a list of keywords specifying what should be placed on the ipc-queue. Defaults to all queue elements.
        toeProcessingOverrides - an ALIST of overrides that change how we deal with processing the assertions. Defaults to no TOE processing overrides.
        Returns:
        the final InferenceSuspendReason
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if a communications error occurs
        CycApiException - if the api request results in a cyc server error

                          throws CycConnectionException,
                                 CycApiException
        This function takes a query specification and iteratively uses the bindings from the query to make assertions. All parameters except querySpec and ipcQueueIdentifier have defaults for null.
        Parameters:
        querySpec - the query specification to process
        overridingQueryProperties - a PLIST of overriding properties for the query
        substitutions - an ALIST of (old . new) indexical pairs
        ipcQueueIdentifier - an integer identifier used to specify the ipc-queue
        ipcQueueElementSpecification - a list of keywords specifying contents of the ipc-queue
        Returns:
        the final InferenceSuspendReason
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if a communications error occurs
        CycApiException - if the api request results in a cyc server error
